doc.after: The Indian Ocean is the third largest of the world s oceanic divisions covering approximately 20 of the water on the Earth s surface 1 It is bounded by Asia on the north on the west by Africa on the east by Australia and on the south by the Southern Ocean or depending on definition by Antarctica 2 Although generally assumed to be named for India 3 4 5 6 early European writers referred to the East Indian Ocean the East Indies being the name given by European travellers collectively to India South East Asia and the Indonesian archipelago 7
